BITCOIN vs ETHEREUM WHITE PAPERS

Aspect                            Bitcoin White Paper                                    Ethereum White Paper
Title                  Bitcoin: A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System      A Next-Generation Smart Contract and Decentralized Application Platform
Author                 Satoshi Nakamoto                                    Vitalik Buterin
Year Published         2008                                                2013
Primary Goal           Create decentralized digital money                  Create programmable blockchain platform
Main Focus             Peer-to-peer electronic cash                        Smart contracts & decentralized applications
Core Problem           Addressed Trust in financial intermediaries         Limited programmability of Bitcoin
Key Innovation         Blockchain + Proof of Work                          Smart contracts + Ethereum Virtual Machine
Native Currency        Bitcoin (BTC)                                       Ether (ETH)
Transaction Purpose    Transfer of value                                   Value transfer + computation
Programming Capability  Very limited scripting                             Fully programmable
Smart Contracts        Not supported                                       Fully supported
Blockchain Usage       Payments only                                       DApps, DeFi, NFTs, DAOs
Consensus (Originally) Proof of Work                                       Proof of Work
Current Consensus      Proof of Work                                       Proof of Stake
Supply Limit           Fixed (21 million BTC)                              No fixed maximum supply
Security Model         Hash-based mining                                   Gas-based execution
Privacy Approach       Pseudonymous                                        Pseudonymous
Network Vision         Digital gold & currency                             Decentralized world computer


 
 
Key Differences Explained Simply
  Bitcoin White Paper focuses on money
  Ethereum White Paper focuses on applications
  Bitcoin replaces banks
  Ethereum replaces centralized platforms
  Bitcoin is store of value
  Ethereum is programmable infrastructure



One-Line:
Bitcoin White Paper:
 Introduces a decentralized peer-to-peer electronic cash system without intermediaries.
Ethereum White Paper:
 Introduces a programmable blockchain platform for smart contracts and decentralized applications.

The Bitcoin White Paper laid the foundation for decentralized digital currency, while the Ethereum White Paper expanded blockchain technology by introducing programmability and smart contracts, enabling modern Web3 ecosystems.

 

